iament agreed last year to make the fund sell out of companies that get more than 30 percent of their business from coal. The fund is also limiting investments in firms with high greenhouse gas emissions.\n                  \"Big money is now starting to move away from fossil fuels,\"  Martin Norman, director of Greenpeace's Nordic Finance Campaign, said in a statement, adding that \"others should follow\".\n                  Norway's fund, built up from the country's oil and gas production revenues, said it sold stakes in 11 companies involved in mining coal for power production and 16 power generators using coal.   (Reporting by Alister Doyle; Editing by Alexander Smith)\n\n\n","keywords":[{"relevance":"0.9372","sentiment":{"type":"neutral"},"keywords_text":"sovereign wealth fund"},{"relevance":"0.879115","sentiment":{"type":"negative","score":"-0.519841"},"keywords_text":"palm oil plantations"},{"relevance":"0.829662","sentiment":{"type":"negative","score":"-0.327027"},"keywords_text":"greenhouse gas emissions"},{"relevance":"0.812509","sentiment":{"type":"positive","score":"0.263181"},"keywords_text":"Nordic Finance Campaign"},{"relevance":"0.798967","sentiment":{"type":"negative","score":"-0.214561"},"keywords_text":"gas production revenues"},{"relevance":"0.634771","sentiment":{"type":"negative","score":"-0.519841"},"keywords_text":"fast-growing trees"},{"relevance":"0.627733","sentiment":{"type":"neutral"},"keywords_text":"climate change"},{"relevance":"0.622631","sentiment":{"type":"neutral"},"keywords_text":"Alister Doyle"},{"relevance":"0.61933","sentiment":{"type":"negative","score":"-0.525646"},"keywords_text":"big investors"},{"relevance":"0.618055","sentiment":{"type":"neutral"},"keywords_text":"coal"},{"relevance":"0.610992","sentiment":{"type":"negative","score":"-0.519841"},"keywords_text":"tropical forests"},{"relevance":"0.589715","sentiment":{"type":"neutral"},"keywords_text":"fossil fuels"},{"relevance":"0.578089","sentiment":{"type":"positive",